ype\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Maven setup guidance**\\n\\nI need to look into the dependencies for using the maven-resolver-supplier, which is meant to be \\\"batteries included,\\\" including basic connectors and transport options. It's important to note that this library is for Maven, not resolver 2.0. For testing, I could set up a temporary local repository by adjusting the session localRepositoryManager. I should avoid network operations and create a minimal POM file with a temp file repository. Also, it's essential to configure the RepositorySystemSession correctly.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining agent guidance in tests**\\n\\nI'm wondering if I need to provide specific agent guidance since the deterministic coverage might already address dependencies. The generated tests definitely require a LocalRepositoryManager configuration. I think setting up the environment, system properties, and test guidance is important to ensure everything works smoothly. It's all about making sure the tests are correctly set up to avoid any hiccups later on!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Maven setup**\\n\\nI’m considering how to test the implementation of version resolver metadata. Including the HTTP transport might be necessary since most remote setups use it, but I can manage without it if needed. I realize there are risks in avoiding network dependencies, as it might affect the tests hitting Maven Central. I’ll summarize my conclusions in a concise JSON object without markdown, ensuring any necessary dependencies are handled properly, and keep the setup flexible.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"The artifact is a Maven Resolver provider: its main artifact supplies Maven-specific descriptor/version readers and session utilities, but documentation and source state that clients must add repository connectors/transports before real repository resolution works. Meaningful hermetic coverage should use a temporary file-based Maven repository, which requires extra Resolver connector and file transport test dependencies.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven.resolver:maven-resolver-connector-basic:1.9.25\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Maven 3.9.12 manages Resolver 1.9.25, and MavenRepositorySystemUtils only registers provider services; artifact/metadata resolution needs a RepositoryConnectorFactory.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven.resolver:maven-resolver-transport-file:1.9.25\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Hermetic tests can exercise descriptor/version resolution against a temporary file:// Maven repository without live network access, but Resolver needs a file transporter implementation for that.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Use a temporary local repository/session and a temporary file:// remote repository with minimal POM/metadata fixtures. Configure the RepositorySystem from MavenRepositorySystemUtils.newServiceLocator(), register the available connector/transport services, and set a LocalRepositoryManager rooted in a temp directory. Avoid live Maven Central/network resolution. Avoid covering MavenResolverModule unless explicit Guice/Guava optional dependencies are intentionally added.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Without connector and transport implementations, tests that call RepositorySystem resolution APIs will fail with missing connector/transporter services rather than exercising this provider.\",\n    \"The public MavenResolverModule class references optional Guice classes that are not part of the normal transitive runtime classpath; generated tests should avoid it unless additional optional dependencies are added.\",\n    \"HTTP transport is not included because hermetic tests should use file:// repositories; tests that choose live HTTP resolution would need org.apache.maven.resolver:maven-resolver-transport-http:1.9.25 and would be less reliable.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_051efef5917e7a4f016a410033288c8196ad04a19c0f788d9a\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 891, "output": 1199, "cacheRead": 19968, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 22058, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782644774946, "responseId": "resp_051efef5917e7a4f016a4100279fe08196bfc837277c44d976"}, "toolResults": []}
